    "body": "# Problem\r\n`gx` does not work on help tags like `|foo|` or `*foo*` even though they link to sections in the online documentation.\r\n\r\n# Solution\r\nMake `gx` in help buffers recognize these tags and open the corresponding page on neovim.io.\r\n\r\ncloses #35420 \r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2025-09-15T22:38:51Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I know this is still WIP, but commenting early to mention that I think the way we should do this is by setting the `url` attribute in the Treesitter highlight query (see e.g. Markdown for an example of this).\r\n\r\nThis gives us `gx` for free *and* makes the help tags clickable with the mouse by using OSC 8.",
